; Reserving $02..$5F keeps Prog8's VARIABLES in $60..$7F (+ main RAM), where
; a kernel call can't reach them -- WITHOUT it a variable landing in that
; range is silently corrupted by the next call. Prog8 honours %zpreserved
; only in the program being compiled, so it cannot be inherited from here;
; every app must repeat the line. (basicsafe pins its SCRATCH_PTR at $22 --
